HEADWORD: home-grown
<hw>home-grown</hw></mhw> <pos>adj.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>grown or produced at home or in a specific locality; --
of plants or animals.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> local.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Originating in a particular place or region; <as>as,
<ex>homegrown</ex> talent</as>; -- applied broadly, to people
(especially people with specific skills), products of manufacture,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Home-keeping</ent>⟦br⟧
